    {
      "id": "5afadf9b_6036c6e1",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/rest/PapRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 44,
      "message": "If we add more endpoints to this controller and some need @Consumes JSON, how does each @ApiOperation know when to @Produces and when to @Consumes. Maybe we still need to add it on @ApiOperation level as well?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1441,
        "name": "Chenfei Gao",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cgao@research.att.com",
        "username": "cgao"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-20 22:03:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "50d9ce12_8d9de0bf",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/rest/PapRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 44,
      "message": "In general, the practice is to add @Produces & @Consumes at the class level to inform the jaxrs implementation (example - jersey) about what format of input/output is supported by the controller (example - json, xml) . And then that gets applied to appropriate API (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) by the jaxrs implementation.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3239,
        "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
        "username": "ramverma"
      },
